<heading id="8F0BBE6AFFDCFFE6FC536297FAD3FB36" box="[915,1318,1177,1202]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093" reason="2">
GENUS 
<taxonomicName id="13FC7285FFDCFFE6FC2B6297FAD3FB36" authority="LEIDY, 1849" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1849" box="[1003,1318,1177,1202]" class="Heterotrichea" family="Nyctotheridae" genus="Nyctotherus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Heterotrichida" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFDCFFE6FC2B6297FB61FB34" box="[1003,1172,1177,1200]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">NYCTOTHERUS</emphasis>
LEIDY, 1849
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9CE65A8DFFDCFFE5FCE962CFFD3DFF7D" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="1094" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D4430906FFDCFFE6FCE962CFFC16F9AC" blockId="21.[809,1425,1217,1576]" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFDCFFE6FCE962CFFBDAFB52" box="[809,1071,1217,1238]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">Improved diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body ovate; macronucleus usually oriented with its longer axis perpendicularly to main body axis; karyophore present, typically attached to right and left body sides; somatic ciliature holotrichous, ventral rows gradually shortened along oral groove, dorsal rows form a median suture in anterior and posterior body region; oral groove begins subapically and extends along left body margin to about mid-body; peristomial funnel (vestibulum) inverted J-shaped; adoral zone of membranelles runs in oral groove then plunges into vestibulum to extend on its right side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4430906FFDCFFE6FCE9605CFB2AF901" blockId="21.[809,1423,1617,1670]" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFDCFFE6FCE9605CFC25F9E3" box="[809,976,1618,1639]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">
<typeStatus id="0B47B7A4FFDCFFE6FCE9605CFC96F9E3" box="[809,867,1618,1639]" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="13FC7285FFDCFFE6FC20605FFA92F9E2" authority="Leidy, 1849" authorityName="Leidy" authorityYear="1849" box="[992,1383,1617,1639]" class="Heterotrichea" family="Nyctotheridae" genus="Nyctotherus" kingdom="Chromista" order="Heterotrichida" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="velox">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFDCFFE6FC20605FFB30F9E2" box="[992,1221,1617,1638]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">Nyctotherus velox</emphasis>
Leidy, 1849
</taxonomicName>
by monotypy (Article 68.3 of 
<bibRefCitation id="B06D74F7FFDCFFE6FB8E607EFB3AF901" author="ICZN" box="[1102,1231,1648,1669]" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093" refId="ref17784" refString="ICZN. 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature, 4 th edn. London: International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature." type="book" year="1999">ICZN, 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4430906FFDCFFE5FCE960A0FD3DFF7D" blockId="21.[809,1425,1710,1794]" lastBlockId="22.[163,779,197,250]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="1094" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFDCFFE6FCE960A0FC5FF947" box="[809,938,1710,1731]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">Etymology:</emphasis>
Not provided in the original description. Composed of the Greek prefix 
<emphasis id="E688D514FFDCFFE6FB4560C3FB4FF966" box="[1157,1210,1741,1762]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">nukt</emphasis>
- (
<emphasis id="E688D514FFDCFFE6FB1260C0FAE6F967" box="[1234,1299,1742,1763]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">νυΚΤ-</emphasis>
; dark) and the Greek noun 
<emphasis id="E688D514FFDCFFE6FC2F60E2FBB0F885" box="[1007,1093,1772,1793]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">thēríon</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="E688D514FFDCFFE6FB9760E2FB72F885" box="[1111,1159,1772,1793]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="1093">θηρ</emphasis>
ῐ[n]; animal), likely alluding to the habitat (i.e. hindgut) of 
<typeStatus id="0B47B7A4FFDFFFE5FDB766C8FD5FFF5F" box="[631,682,198,219]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1094">type</typeStatus>
species. Masculine gender (Article 30.1.3 of 
<bibRefCitation id="B06D74F7FFDFFFE5FDF766EAFD4DFF7D" author="ICZN" box="[567,696,228,249]" pageId="22" pageNumber="1094" refId="ref17784" refString="ICZN. 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature, 4 th edn. London: International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature." type="book" year="1999">ICZN, 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
